alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 04 at 10:58PM PDT until November 06 at 5:38AM PDT by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .Five to seven inches of rain fell in the Central Cascades Friday. The heavy rain has ended. This amount of rain will push the Snoqualmie River near Carnation above flood stage Friday evening with the river cresting Saturday morning. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL EARLY SUNDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until early Sunday morning. * IMPACTS...At 56.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will cause widespread flooding from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall... inundating much of the farm land and numerous roads. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:15 PM PDT Friday the stage was 53.2 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage late this evening to a crest of 57.9 feet late tomorrow morning. It will then fall below flood stage Saturday night. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by Saturday morning at 700 AM PDT.
